text:
One of the #ausbushcraftmag field production computers. It's a #Panasonic #Toughbook #fullyrugged laptop. The screen converts to a tablet configuration. It has touchscreen input or mouse and keyboard. Built in 3G wireless card for data anywhere there's a Telstra tower, GPS, and a battery life tested to be over 4 hours (so far). The laptop is rated to #IP65, it is completely dustproof and rainproof. It is also built to #MILSTD810G which gives the unit very high shock and drop protection. It's very rugged, but not terribly high spec. It's definitely not a desktop replacement but allows us to crunch images, write and produce high quality PDF documents in the middle of nowhere, in a duststorm or in the middle of a thunder storm while dropping the unit onto rocks from head height ;-) You know what they say, better to have it and not need it... etc. For any Toughbook geeks out there, this one is a CF-19 Mk3. Ex-Australian Defence department.
#fieldmediaproduction
#amwriting
#AustralianBushcraftMagazine

text: The @panasonicusa #toughbook CF-54 laptop is quite literally a tank's body concealing the brainpower of a computing device. It is aimed strictly at B2B customers who need something incredibly tough as their daily driver. Prices begin at ₹1.2 lacs. #laptop

@Panasonic has launched the #Toughbook CF-20 hybrid laptop in India. At an estimated priced of Rs. 2.25 lakhs, the device will be available from August. the laptop features a rugged design and is IP65 certified for dust and water resistance. The laptop comes with Windows 10 pre-installed and features a 10.1-inch WUXGA display with a resolution of 1920 x 1200. text:
One of the #ausbushcraftmag field production computers. It's a #Panasonic #Toughbook #fullyrugged laptop. The screen converts to a tablet configuration. It has touchscreen input or mouse and keyboard. Built in 3G wireless card for data anywhere there's a Telstra tower, GPS, and a battery life tested to be over 4 hours (so far). The laptop is rated to #IP65, it is completely dustproof and rainproof. It is also built to #MILSTD810G which gives the unit very high shock and drop protection. It's very rugged, but not terribly high spec. It's definitely not a desktop replacement but allows us to crunch images, write and produce high quality PDF documents in the middle of nowhere, in a duststorm or in the middle of a thunder storm while dropping the unit onto rocks from head height ;-) You know what they say, better to have it and not need it... etc. For any Toughbook geeks out there, this one is a CF-19 Mk3. Ex-Australian Defence department.
